txt.en: Gárferth
'That is all for today. Farewell, Reeve of Wildermore.'
Edsig
'Here are the last of your sons.'
'Gárferth! Edsig! What have you done to them?'
Gársig's Home
Defender
'It was a very brief attack, Reeve Gárwig.'
'No more than these dead Orcs you see here.'
'Are you here to murder me too, giant?'
'They threw themselves at the gate, and then... nothing. It was done.'
'Why not be done with it? Kill me, and leave Wildermore forever.'
'Hm. With such a small force, they could have no hope of capturing Forlaw.'
'No, Gárwig! We will not let him have you!'
'It was an odd move, even for Orcs.'
'Ha! Do not flatter yourselves.'
'Oh no. That... that chill. It is just like....'
'If I was here to kill the old man, you could not stop me.'
'I am here to deliver a gift.'
'I greet you, Gárwig, Reeve of Wildermore.'
